
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: springboot
  labels:
    app: springboot
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: springboot
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: springboot
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: springboot
        image: mylandmarktech/spring-boot-mongo
        ports:
        - containerPort: 8080
        env:
        - name: MONGO_DB_USERNAME
          valueFrom:
            secretKeyRef:
              name: spring-secret
              key: mongo-root-username
        - name: MONGO_DB_PASSWORD
          valueFrom:
            secretKeyRef:
              name: spring-secret
              key: mongo-root-password
        - name: MONGO_DB_HOSTNAME
          valueFrom:
            configMapKeyRef:
              name: spring-configmap
              key: database_url

---
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: spring-service
spec:
  selector:
    app: springboot
  type: LoadBalancer
  ports:
    - protocol: TCP
      port: 8080
      targetPort: 8080
      nodePort: 30000
~                      
HOW TO WRITE YAML FILE FOR IMAGE IN PRIVATE REPOSITORY
1. Create a secret for your docker credential



When creating deployment object for you application for an image in private repository. You have to pass the "imagePullSecrets" it could be above
the container name or below as it is below:
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: private-reg
spec:
  containers:
  - name: private-reg-container
    image: <your-private-image>
  imagePullSecrets:
  - name: regcred
